\section{Design philosophy}{

Modelers think in models, not in function calls.  \code{alloy} follows the
principle that \code{fitMod(y ~ x, data, fitfn = "logit")} is preferable to
\code{glm(y ~ x, data, family = "binomial")} – the intent is stated directly,
and the package handles package-specific quirks, defaults, and post-processing
transparently.  Output follows Stata conventions where applicable.
}

